Group members: Cooper Bowman, Lucien Verdun, Ashley Andrade

R1: 	  The solution must support missiles launched by the user.
R1.A:	  The solution must initiate a missle launch when the user clicks the right mouse button.
		    PRECONDITION:	  There are no missiles on the screen.
		    ACTION:			    The user clicks the right mouse button.
		    POSTCONDITION:	The solution launches a single missile and there is one missile on the screen.
		
		    PRECONDITION:	There is a missile on the screen.
		    ACTION:			The user clicks the right mouse button.
		    POSTCODITION:	The solution launches a single missile and there are two missiles on the screen.
		
		    PRECONDITION:	There are two missiles present on the screen.
		    ACTION:			The user clicks the right mouse button.
		    POSTCODITION:	The solution launches a single missile and there are three missiles on the screen.
		
		    PRECONDITION:	There are no missiles on the screen.
		    ACTION:			The user presses H on the keyboard.
		    POSTCODITION:	The solution does not launch a missile.
		
		    PRECONDITION:	There are no missiles on the screen.
		    ACTION:			The user presses S on the keyboard.
		    POSTCODITION:	The solution does not launch a missile.
		
		    PRECONDITION:	There are no missiles on the screen.
		    ACTION:			The user presses C on the keyboard.
		    POSTCODITION:	The solution does not launch a missile.
		
		    PRECONDITION:	There are no missiles on the screen.
		    ACTION:			The user presses the up arrow key on the keyboard.
		    POSTCODITION:	The solution does not launch a missile.
		
		    PRECONDITION:	There are no missiles on the screen.
		    ACTION:			The user presses 8 on the keyboard.
		    POSTCODITION:	The solution does not launch a missile.
		
		    PRECONDITION:	There are no missiles on the screen.
		    ACTION:			The user does not interact with the mouse or keyboard.
		    POSTCODITION:	There are no missiles on the screen.
		
R1.B:	  The solution must initiate a missle launch when the user clicks the space bar.
		    PRECONDITION:	There are no missiles present on the screen.
		    ACTION:			User presses the spacebar.
		    POSTCONDITION:	The solution launches a single missile and there is one missile on the screen.
		
		    PRECONDITION:	There is a missile present on the screen.
		    ACTION:			The user presses the spacebar.
		    POSTCODITION:	The solution launches a single missile and there are two missiles on the screen.
		
		    PRECONDITION:	There are two missiles present on the screen.
		    ACTION:			The user presses the spacebar.
		    POSTCODITION:	The solution launches a single missile and there are three missiles on the screen.
		
		    PRECONDITION:	There are no missiles on the screen.
		    ACTION:			The user presses Y on the keyboard.
		    POSTCODITION:	The solution does not launch a missile.
		
		    PRECONDITION:	There are no missiles on the screen.
	    	ACTION:			The user presses 3 on the keyboard.
	    	POSTCODITION:	The solution does not launch a missile.
		
    		PRECONDITION:	There are no missiles on the screen.
	    	ACTION:			The user presses B on the keyboard.
		    POSTCODITION:	The solution does not launch a missile.
		
	    	PRECONDITION:	There are no missiles on the screen.
    		ACTION:			The user presses the left arrow key on the keyboard.
    		POSTCODITION:	The solution does not launch a missile.
		
    		PRECONDITION:	There are no missiles on the screen.
    		ACTION:			The user presses 8 on the keyboard.
    		POSTCODITION:	The solution does not launch a missile.
		
R1.C:	  The solution must limit the number of active missiles on the scren to no more than five (5) at any given time. (an "active missile" is any missile currently being displayed on the screen)
	    	PRECONDITION:	There are no missiles on the screen.
	    	ACTION:			The user clicks the right mouse button.
    		POSTCONDITION:	The solution launches a single missile and there is one missile on the screen.
		
    		PRECONDITION:	There is one missile on the screen.
    		ACTION:			The user clicks the right mouse button.
    		POSTCONDITION:	The solution launches a single missile and there are two missile on the screen.
		
    		PRECONDITION:	There are two missiles on the screen.
    		ACTION:			The user clicks the right mouse button.
    		POSTCONDITION:	The solution launches a single missile and there are three missiles on the screen.
		
    		PRECONDITION:	There are three missiles on the screen.
    		ACTION:			The user clicks the right mouse button.
    		POSTCONDITION:	The solution launches a single missile and there are four missiles on the screen.
		
    		PRECONDITION:	There are four missiles on the screen.
    		ACTION:			The user clicks the right mouse button.
    		POSTCONDITION:	The solution launches a single missile and there are five missiles on the screen.
    		
	    	PRECONDITION:	There are five missiles on the screen.
	    	ACTION:			The user clicks the right mouse button.
	    	POSTCONDITION:	The solution does not launch any missiles and there are five missiles on the screen.
		
R2:   	The solution must support ships launched by the solution.
R2.A:  	The solution must initiate a ship launch when the system detects there are no active ships.
	    	PRECONDITION:	No ships active
		    ACTION:			Initiate a ship launch
	    	POSTCONDITION:	Ship launched
		
    		PRECONDITION:	Ships active
	    	ACTION			No ship launch
	    	POSTCONDITION	No new ship added
		
R2.B:	  The solution must suuport multiple types of ships based on a configurable table.
	    	PRECONDITION:	No configuration value given
	    	ACTION:			No different ship types spawned
	    	POSTCONDITION:	No different ships on screen
		
	    	PRECONDITION:	Proper configuration value given
    		ACTION:			Different ships spawned
    		POSTCONDITION:	Different ships on screen
		
    		PRECONDITION:	Improper configuration value given
    		ACTION:			Default to standard ship
    		POSTCONDITION:	Standard ship spawns
		
R2.C:  	The solution must display the appropriate image based on the type of ship when the ship is active.
	    	PRECONDITION:	Type of ship provided and image can be accessed
    		ACTION:			Corresponding ship type image found
    		POSTCONDITION:	Ship image generated on screen
		
    		PRECONDITION:	Type of ship not provided and image can be accessed
    		ACTION:			Corresponding ship type not found
    		POSTCONDITION:	Generic ship image generated on screen
		
    		PRECONDITION:	Type of ship provided and image cannot be accessed
    		ACTION:			Corresponding ship image type not found
    		POSTCONDITION:	Generic ship image generated on screen
		
    		PRECONDITION:	Neither ship type or image provided
    		ACTION:			Corresponding ship type nor image found, find genreic image; generate error
    		POSTCONDITION:	Ships spawned use generic image in place
		
    		PRECONDITION:	No images provided, no generic provided, no ship type provided
    		ACTION:			Fatal error generated, populate screen with error
    		POSTCONDITION:	Solution ends

R3:		  The solution must end the game when the “hit” count has reached ten (10)
    		PRECONDITION: 	The solution is active and the hit counter has not reached ten
    		ACTION: 		The hit counter reaches 10
    		POSTCONDITION: 	The game ends

    		PRECONDITION: 	The solution is active and the hit counter has not reached ten
    		ACTION: 		The user stops playing and does not hit any buttons
    		POSTCONDITION: 	The game ends after 5 minutes

	    	PRECONDITION: 	The solution is active and the hit counter has not reached ten
	    	ACTION: 		The user continues launching missiles but the hit counter never reaches 10
	    	POSTCONDITION: 	The game does not end


R4:	  	The solution must end the game when the user clicks the left mouse button
    		PRECONDITION: 	The solution is active and the user has not clicked the left mouse button
    		ACTION: 		The user clicks the left mouse button
    		POSTCONDITION: 	The game ends

	    	PRECONDITION: 	The solution is active and the user has not clicked the left mouse button
	    	ACTION: 		The user does not click anything or hit any buttons
    		POSTCONDITION: 	The game ends after 5 minutes

    		PRECONDITION: 	The solution is active, the user has not clicked the left mouse button, and the user is launching missiles but the hit counter has not reached 10
    		ACTION: 		The user continues launching missiles but the hit counter never reaches 10
    		POSTCONDITION: 	The game does not end
    

R5: 	  The solution must end the game when the user clicks the esc button
	    	PRECONDITION: 	The solution is active and the user has not pressed the esc button
    		ACTION: 		The user presses the esc button
    		POSTCONDITION: 	The game ends

    		PRECONDITION: 	The solution is active and the user has not pressed the esc button
    		ACTION: 		The user does not click anything or hit any buttons
    		POSTCONDITION: 	The game ends after 5 minutes

	    	PRECONDITION: 	The solution is active, the user has not pressed the esc button, and the user is launching missiles but the hit counter has not reached 10
    		ACTION: 		The user continues launching missiles but the hit counter never reaches 10
    		POSTCONDITION: 	The game does not end


R6:	  	The solution must end the game if the user has not initiated a missile launch in the last 5 minutes.
	    	PRECONDITION: 	The solution is active and the user does not launch any missiles
    		ACTION: 		The user continues to not launch missiles for 5 minutes
    		POSTCONDITION: 	The game ends
  
    		PRECONDITION: 	The solution is active and the user does launch missiles
    		ACTION: 		The user continues to launches missiles and raises the hit counter to 10
    		POSTCONDITION: 	The game ends

	    	PRECONDITION: 	The solution is active and the user does launch missiles
	    	ACTION: 		The user continues to launch missiles but does not raise the hit count to 10
	    	POSTCONDITION: 	The game does not end
